===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|cerubin|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{term|cherub|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|χερούβ|lang=grc}}, ultimately from {{etyl|he|en}} {{term|כרוב| כְּרוּב|tr= kerúv|lang=he|sc=Hebr}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|chĕrʹəb}}, {{IPA|/ˈtʃɛrəb/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|cherubim}}

# A winged creature represented over 90 times in the [[Bible]] as attending on God, later seen as the second highest order of [[angels]], ranked above [[throne]]s and below [[seraph]]im. First mention is in [http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Bible_%28World_English%29/Genesis#Chapter_3 Genesis 3:24]
# A statue or other depiction of such a being, typically in the form of a winged child.
# {{context|figuratively|lang=en}} A person, especially a child, seen as being particularly innocent or angelic.

